AssociateAwsAccountWithPartnerAccount.name: AssociateAwsAccountWithPartnerAccount
AssociateAwsAccountWithPartnerAccount.documentation: Associates a partner account with your AWS account.

AssociateWirelessDeviceWithThing.name: AssociateWirelessDeviceWithThing
AssociateWirelessDeviceWithThing.documentation: Associates a wireless device with a thing.

AssociateWirelessGatewayWithCertificate.name: AssociateWirelessGatewayWithCertificate
AssociateWirelessGatewayWithCertificate.documentation: Associates a wireless gateway with a certificate.

AssociateWirelessGatewayWithThing.name: AssociateWirelessGatewayWithThing
AssociateWirelessGatewayWithThing.documentation: Associates a wireless gateway with a thing.

CreateDestination.name: CreateDestination
CreateDestination.documentation: Creates a new destination that maps a device message to an AWS IoT rule.

CreateWirelessGatewayTask.name: CreateWirelessGatewayTask
CreateWirelessGatewayTask.documentation: Creates a task for a wireless gateway.

DeleteWirelessGatewayTaskDefinition.name: DeleteWirelessGatewayTaskDefinition
DeleteWirelessGatewayTaskDefinition.documentation: Deletes a wireless gateway task definition. Deleting this task definition does not affect tasks that are currently in progress.

DisassociateAwsAccountFromPartnerAccount.name: DisassociateAwsAccountFromPartnerAccount
DisassociateAwsAccountFromPartnerAccount.documentation: Disassociates your AWS account from a partner account. If PartnerAccountId and PartnerType are null, disassociates your AWS account from all partner accounts.

DisassociateWirelessDeviceFromThing.name: DisassociateWirelessDeviceFromThing
DisassociateWirelessDeviceFromThing.documentation: Disassociates a wireless device from its currently associated thing.

DisassociateWirelessGatewayFromCertifica.name: DisassociateWirelessGatewayFromCertificate
DisassociateWirelessGatewayFromCertifica.documentation: Disassociates a wireless gateway from its currently associated certificate.

DisassociateWirelessGatewayFromThing.name: DisassociateWirelessGatewayFromThing
DisassociateWirelessGatewayFromThing.documentation: Disassociates a wireless gateway from its currently associated thing.

GetLogLevelsByResourceTypes.name: GetLogLevelsByResourceTypes
GetLogLevelsByResourceTypes.documentation: Returns current default log levels or log levels by resource types. Based on resource types, log levels can be for wireless device log options or wireless gateway log options.

GetPartnerAccount.name: GetPartnerAccount
GetPartnerAccount.documentation: Gets information about a partner account. If PartnerAccountId and PartnerType are null, returns all partner accounts.

GetResourceLogLevel.name: GetResourceLogLevel
GetResourceLogLevel.documentation: Fetches the log-level override, if any, for a given resource-ID and resource-type. It can be used for a wireless device or a wireless gateway.

GetServiceEndpoint.name: GetServiceEndpoint
GetServiceEndpoint.documentation: Gets the account-specific endpoint for Configuration and Update Server (CUPS) protocol or LoRaWAN Network Server (LNS) connections.

GetWirelessDeviceStatistics.name: GetWirelessDeviceStatistics
GetWirelessDeviceStatistics.documentation: Gets operating information about a wireless device.

GetWirelessGatewayCertificate.name: GetWirelessGatewayCertificate
GetWirelessGatewayCertificate.documentation: Gets the ID of the certificate that is currently associated with a wireless gateway.

GetWirelessGatewayFirmwareInformation.name: GetWirelessGatewayFirmwareInformation
GetWirelessGatewayFirmwareInformation.documentation: Gets the firmware version and other information about a wireless gateway.

GetWirelessGatewayStatistics.name: GetWirelessGatewayStatistics
GetWirelessGatewayStatistics.documentation: Gets operating information about a wireless gateway.

GetWirelessGatewayTask.name: GetWirelessGatewayTask
GetWirelessGatewayTask.documentation: Gets information about a wireless gateway task.

GetWirelessGatewayTaskDefinition.name: GetWirelessGatewayTaskDefinition
GetWirelessGatewayTaskDefinition.documentation: Gets information about a wireless gateway task definition.

ListDestinations.name: ListDestinations
ListDestinations.documentation: Lists the destinations registered to your AWS account.

ListDeviceProfiles.name: ListDeviceProfiles
ListDeviceProfiles.documentation: Lists the device profiles registered to your AWS account.

ListPartnerAccounts.name: ListPartnerAccounts
ListPartnerAccounts.documentation: Lists the partner accounts associated with your AWS account.

ListServiceProfiles.name: ListServiceProfiles
ListServiceProfiles.documentation: Lists the service profiles registered to your AWS account.

ListTagsForResource.name: ListTagsForResource
ListTagsForResource.documentation: Lists the tags (metadata) you have assigned to the resource.

ListWirelessDevices.name: ListWirelessDevices
ListWirelessDevices.documentation: Lists the wireless devices registered to your AWS account.

ListWirelessGatewayTaskDefinitions.name: ListWirelessGatewayTaskDefinitions
ListWirelessGatewayTaskDefinitions.documentation: List the wireless gateway tasks definitions registered to your AWS account.

ListWirelessGateways.name: ListWirelessGateways
ListWirelessGateways.documentation: Lists the wireless gateways registered to your AWS account.

PutResourceLogLevel.name: PutResourceLogLevel
PutResourceLogLevel.documentation: Sets the log-level override for a resource-ID and resource-type. This option can be specified for a wireless gateway or a wireless device. A limit of 200 log level override can be set per account.

ResetAllResourceLogLevels.name: ResetAllResourceLogLevels
ResetAllResourceLogLevels.documentation: Removes the log-level overrides for all resources; both wireless devices and wireless gateways.

ResetResourceLogLevel.name: ResetResourceLogLevel
ResetResourceLogLevel.documentation: Removes the log-level override, if any, for a specific resource-ID and resource-type. It can be used for a wireless device or a wireless gateway.

SendDataToWirelessDevice.name: SendDataToWirelessDevice
SendDataToWirelessDevice.documentation: Sends a decrypted application data frame to a device.

TestWirelessDevice.name: TestWirelessDevice
TestWirelessDevice.documentation: Simulates a provisioned device by sending an uplink data payload of Hello.

UntagResource.name: UntagResource
UntagResource.documentation: Removes one or more tags from a resource.

UpdateLogLevelsByResourceTypes.name: UpdateLogLevelsByResourceTypes
UpdateLogLevelsByResourceTypes.documentation: Set default log level, or log levels by resource types. This can be for wireless device log options or wireless gateways log options and is used to control the log messages that'll be displayed in CloudWatch.

AbpV1_0_x.documentation: ABP device object for LoRaWAN specification v1.0.x

AbpV1_1.documentation: ABP device object for LoRaWAN specification v1.1
